==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poppit
<hw>Pop"pit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a small plastic bead
with opposed holes and protuberant knobs, so shaped that the beads may
be fastened to each other in chains and detached easily, and can be used
to form variable-length chains for use as necklaces, bracelets, or other
ornamental objects. Also called <altname>poppet</altname> and
<altname>poppit bead</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Popple</ent>⟦br⟧
